total_subquestions_ys: Q1: Identify the unique numbers in the grid.
Q2: Count the frequency of each unique number in each quadrant of the grid.
Q3: Identify the number with the highest frequency in each quadrant.
Q4: Create a new 4x4 grid where each quadrant is filled with the number that had the highest frequency in the corresponding quadrant of the input grid.
Q5: If there is a tie in the frequency count, fill the quadrant with the number that comes first when reading the grid from left to right, top to bottom.
Q1: Identify the unique numbers in the grid.
Q2: Count the frequency of each unique number in each row.
Q3: Identify the number with the highest frequency in each row.
Q4: Replace the number with the highest frequency with the number that has the second highest frequency in the same row.
Q5: If there is a tie for the highest frequency, replace the number with the highest value.
Q6: If there is a tie for the second highest frequency, replace the number with the lowest value.
Q7: Repeat the process for each row to generate the output grid.
Q1: Identify the unique numbers in the grid.
Q2: Count the frequency of each unique number in each quadrant of the grid.
Q3: Identify the number with the highest frequency in each quadrant.
Q4: Create a new 4x4 grid where each quadrant is filled with the number identified in Q3.
Q5: If there is a tie in the frequency count in Q3, fill the quadrant with the number that appears first in the reading order (top to bottom, left to right).
Q6: If a quadrant does not contain any numbers (only zeros), fill it with zeros in the output grid.
